etymologies: early 17th century; earliest use found in Philemon Holland (1552–1637), translator. From post-classical Latin nobilitation-, nobilitatio ennoblement from classical Latin nōbilitāt-, past participial stem of nōbilitāre + -iō. Compare Middle French nobilitation action of ennobling

definitions: The action of ennobling a person, ennoblement; an instance of this.
